{
  "id": "asm-working-hours",
  "kind": "problem",
  "title": "Progressive Working Hours Register",
  "difficulty": "medium",
  "concepts": [
    "simulation",
    "stateful design",
    "interval accounting",
    "temporal state"
  ],
  "prompt": "Implement a small working-hours register driven by an operation list. `solution(queries)` receives a list of queries; each query is a list of strings `[OP, ...args]`. Return a list with one string result per query, in order. Worker ids and positions are case-sensitive strings. Timestamps and compensation values are non-negative integers given as strings. Compensation is a pay rate per timestamp unit, so a completed session from `start` to `end` at compensation `c` earns `(end - start) * c` before any later special-pay rules.\n\n**Level 1 operations**\n\n- `[\"ADD_WORKER\", workerId, position, compensation]` — add a worker who starts outside the office. Return `\"true\"`, or `\"false\"` if `workerId` already exists.\n- `[\"REGISTER\", workerId, timestamp]` — record that the worker entered or left the office. Register calls are given in increasing timestamp order. If the worker does not exist, return `\"invalid_request\"`. Otherwise toggle their office state and return `\"registered\"`.\n- `[\"GET\", workerId]` — return the total time spent in the office across completed sessions as a string, or `\"\"` if the worker does not exist. An open session does not count until it is closed.\n\nLater levels add rankings, promotions, salary calculation, and special pay periods. Structure the solution around workers and completed intervals so the later features do not require a rewrite.",
  "signature": {
    "name": "solution",
    "inputs": [
      {
        "name": "queries",
        "type": {
          "type": "array",
          "items": {
            "type": "array",
            "items": {
              "type": "string"
            }
          }
        }
      }
    ],
    "output": {
      "type": "array",
      "items": {
        "type": "string"
      }
    }
  },
  "tests": [
    {
      "name": "l1-empty",
      "args": [
        []
      ],
      "expected": [],
      "visibility": "visible"
    },
