    {
      "id": "l3-promotions-salary",
      "title": "Promotions and Salary",
      "prompt": "Extend the register with promotions and salary calculation. All earlier operations keep working.\n\n**New operations**\n\n- `[\"PROMOTE\", workerId, newPosition, newCompensation, startTimestamp]` — schedule a promotion for `workerId`. Return `\"success\"`, or `\"invalid_request\"` if the worker does not exist or already has a pending promotion. A pending promotion applies when that worker next enters the office at a timestamp greater than or equal to `startTimestamp`. It does not affect a session already in progress.\n- `[\"CALC_SALARY\", workerId, startTimestamp, endTimestamp]` — return the salary earned by that worker over the half-open interval `[startTimestamp, endTimestamp)`, or `\"\"` if the worker does not exist. Salary is calculated from completed sessions only, using the position and compensation active when each session began. If a completed session only partly overlaps the requested interval, count only the overlapping portion. Compensation is paid per timestamp unit, so the contribution of a session segment is `overlapDuration * compensation`.\n\n`TOP_N_WORKERS` has no timestamp argument. It reads the current register state after all previous queries have been processed: filter by each worker's current position, then rank by completed time worked in that same current position. Pending promotions do not change a worker's current position until they are applied by a later `REGISTER` entry event.",
      "tests": [
        {
          "name": "l3-promotion-applies-on-next-entry",
          "args": [
            [
              [
                "ADD_WORKER",
                "Ann",
                "engineer",
                "10"
              ],
              [
                "REGISTER",
                "Ann",
                "0"
              ],
              [
                "REGISTER",
                "Ann",
                "10"
              ],
              [
                "PROMOTE",
                "Ann",
                "senior",
                "20",
                "15"
              ],
              [
                "REGISTER",
                "Ann",
                "12"
              ],
              [
                "REGISTER",
                "Ann",
                "18"
              ],
              [
                "REGISTER",
                "Ann",
                "20"
              ],
              [
                "REGISTER",
                "Ann",
                "25"
              ],
              [
                "GET",
                "Ann"
              ],
              [
                "TOP_N_WORKERS",
                "2",
                "engineer"
              ],
              [
                "TOP_N_WORKERS",
                "2",
                "senior"
              ],
              [
                "CALC_SALARY",
                "Ann",
                "0",
                "30"
              ]
            ]
          ],
          "expected": [
            "true",
            "registered",
            "registered",
            "success",
            "registered",
            "registered",
            "registered",
            "registered",
            "21",
            "",
            "Ann(5)",
            "260"
          ],
          "visibility": "visible"
        },
